#!N  #!Rshowcon ShowConnections #!N #!N Category #!N #!N  #!Lcatrel,dxall759 h Realization  #!EL  
#!N #!N Function #!N #!N Draws the connective elements of a 
field. #!N #!N Syntax #!CForestGreen #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-courier-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   #!N output 
#!EF = ShowConnections(  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   input #!EF ); #!EF #!N #!N #!EC 
#!N #!N Inputs #!T,1,91,276,461,646  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--14*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   #!N TAB Name TAB Type 
TAB Default TAB Description #!EF #!N TAB input TAB field TAB 
none TAB field whose connection elements #!N TAB - TAB - 
TAB - TAB are to be shown. #!N TAB - TAB 
- TAB - TAB #!EF #!N #!N Outputs #!T,1,161,321,646  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--14*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
#!N TAB Name TAB Type TAB Description #!EF #!N TAB output 
TAB color field TAB renderable connections of input field #!N TAB 
- TAB - TAB #!EF #!N #!N Functional Details #!N #!N 
This module creates a set of renderable lines representing the "connections" 
component of a specified input. #!N #!I0 #!N #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   input #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N specifies the object whose 
connection elements are to be shown. #!I0 #!N #!N #!N #!N 
#!I0 #!N Notes: #!N #!I30 #!N 1. If the input object 
lacks a "colors" component, the module adds a default color to 
the output. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. Position-dependent color and data components 
are passed to the output. Connection-dependent color and data components are 
not passed to the output, because their values along a connection 
line are ill defined. To make the data or colors position-dependent, 
use the Post module. #!I0 #!N #!N #!N #!N Components #!N 
#!N Creates a new "connections" component and adds a "colors" component 
if the input does not already have one. Connection-dependent components are 
not propagated to the output; all other components are. #!N #!N 
